{{Infobox language |name = Bayot |nativename = |states = [[Senegal]], [[Guinea-Bissau]] |speakers = 19,000 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Bak languages|Bak]] |fam4=[[Jola languages|Jola]] |iso3 = bda |glotto = bayo1255 |glottorefname= Bayot |dia1 = Essin }}
'''Bayot''' (Baiot, Baiote, Bayotte) is a language of southern [[Senegal]], southwest of [[Ziguinchor]] in a group of villages near [[Nyassia]], in northwestern [[Guinea-Bissau]], along the Senegalese border, and in [[the Gambia]].
Bayot is the most divergent of the [[Jola languages]], in the [[Senegambian languages|Senegambian branch]] of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] language family.
