'''Peter Hüttner''' (born 10 December 1945, in [[Gothenburg]]) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] actor and writer.<ref name=sfi>{{cite web | title=Peter Hüttner | url=http://www.sfi.se/sv/svensk-film/Filmdatabasen/?type=PERSON&itemid=72082&iv=OVERVIEW | language=Swedish | publisher=[[Swedish Film Institute]] | accessdate=28 January 2010}}</ref>
Hüttner began his theatrical career at [[Folkteatern]] in [[Gothenburg]] 1968 and was subsequently employed on [[Atelierteatern]]. He is trained at the stage school in [[Malmö]] 1969&ndash;73. He has worked on [[Helsingborg City Theatre]], [[Stockholm City Theatre]], [[Gothenburg City Theatre]], [[Riksteatern]] and [[Folkteatern]]. Hüttner is best known for his role as Oljelund in the films about the police [[Martin Beck]].
